 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added
+
+- **Swappable data-layer boundary** (`src/lib/data/`). Typed async fetchers
+  (`getTransactions`, `getCustomers`, `getLedgerStats`, `getMonthlySeries`,
+  `getCloseChecklist`, `getInboxThread`, `getReviewQueue`) plus pure aggregation
+  helpers (`netTotal`, `totalIncome`/`totalExpense`, `pendingReviewCount`,
+  `summarizeSeries`, `monthMarginPct`, `checklistProgress`) sit behind a single
+  boundary. Each module carries a `// Swap this module's body…` contract comment;
+  bodies return the existing mock fixtures today and can be repointed at a real
+  DB/API without touching consumers. Dashboard pages/components now fetch through
+  this layer as async server components.
