+  search, income/expense filtering, sortable Date/Amount/Confidence columns,
+  CSV export of the current view, and empty-state handling — all over the data
+  layer. View preferences (search/filter/sort) persist to localStorage via a
+  Zustand `persist` store (`useLedgerPrefs`).
+
+### Changed
+
+- Dashboard route segment gains `loading.tsx` (ledger-rhythm skeletons) and
+  `error.tsx` (retry boundary) now that its components do async data fetches.
+  Added shared `Skeleton` UI primitives.
+
+### Tests
+
+- 28 new unit tests for the categorization heuristic + defensive model-JSON
+  parser, the data-layer aggregation helpers, and the ledger-view
+  search/filter/sort/CSV transforms (full suite 49 → 77 green).
+
+## [0.6.0] - 2026-05-29
+
+Backward-compatible feature release. Adds the **trial-balance verifier** to the
+ledger — the first primitive that answers "do debits equal credits?" — composing
+the existing ADR 0003 money-arithmetic kernel so balance decisions run through
+the audited integer-minor-unit / half-even path. No breaking changes since
+`0.5.0`; under the pre-1.0 `0.x` policy a feature release increments the
+**minor**, so this lands as `0.6.0`. Bump derived from `git log v0.5.0..HEAD`
+(one `feat` commit, additive, none breaking), not guessed.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Trial-balance verifier** (`isBalanced`, `verifyTrialBalance`, exported via
+  the `@/features/ledger` barrel). Over double-entry rows
+  (`TrialBalanceEntry { account, currency, debit?, credit? }`), `isBalanced`
+  returns `true` when total debits equal total credits at the currency's
+  minor-unit precision; `verifyTrialBalance` returns the full inspection record
+  (`balanced`, `totalDebits`, `totalCredits`, signed `difference`, and
+  `asymmetricAccounts` — accounts active on exactly one side, sorted + unique).
+  Totals fold through `addMoney` and the difference through `subtractMoney`, so
+  precision is recovered (`0.10 + 0.20` vs `0.30` balances) and results stay
+  consistent with stored ledger values. Empty input is vacuously balanced.
+  Fail-loud: it inherits `MoneyArithmeticError` from the arithmetic kernel —
+  `mixed-currency` if rows carry differing currencies, `not-finite` if any
+  amount is non-finite (no new error type). Pure and side-effect-free. Backed by
+  7 new unit tests (full suite 42 → 49 green).
+
+### Notes
+
