+# Release v0.6.0 — Trial-Balance Verifier
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-29
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.5.0 → 0.6.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.6.0` → release commit
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature addition, **no breaking changes** since `0.5.0`.
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the **minor**, so
+this lands as `0.6.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history, not guessed:
+`git log v0.5.0..HEAD` is a single `feat` commit (`725dcc8`, trial-balance
+verifier) — additive, none breaking.
+
+## Headline
+
+The ledger gains its first **balance primitive**: `verifyTrialBalance` answers
+the core double-entry question — *do debits equal credits?* — and does so by
+composing the audited ADR 0003 money kernel (`addMoney` for the side totals,
+`subtractMoney` for the drift), so a balance decision can never disagree with
+the integer-minor-unit / half-even values the ledger already stores.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Trial-balance verifier** (`isBalanced`, `verifyTrialBalance`), exported via
+  the `@/features/ledger` barrel.
+  - Input: double-entry rows `TrialBalanceEntry { account, currency, debit?, credit? }`.
+  - `isBalanced(entries)` → `boolean`: total debits equal total credits at the
+    currency's minor-unit precision. Empty input is vacuously balanced.
+  - `verifyTrialBalance(entries)` → `TrialBalanceResult`: `balanced`,
+    `totalDebits`, `totalCredits`, signed `difference`
+    (`subtractMoney(totalDebits, totalCredits)`, `0` when balanced), and
+    `asymmetricAccounts` (active on exactly one side; sorted, unique).
+  - Precision is recovered through `addMoney` — `0.10 + 0.20` vs `0.30`
+    balances, not a floating-point near-miss.
+  - **Fail-loud**, no new error type: inherits `MoneyArithmeticError` —
+    `mixed-currency` when rows carry differing currencies, `not-finite` when any
+    amount is non-finite.
+  - Pure, side-effect-free. 7 new unit tests (suite 42 → 49 green).
+
+## Bump rationale (auditable)
+
+| Input | Signal | Bump |
+|-------|--------|------|
+| `feat(ledger): add trial-balance verifier` (`725dcc8`) | new backward-compatible API | MINOR |
+| Breaking changes since `v0.5.0`? | none | — |
+
+→ Highest applicable bump = **MINOR** → `0.6.0`.
+
+## Release-quality gate (cleared)
+
+The committed trunk at `725dcc8` was verified in isolation (the working tree
+held unrelated, in-progress, un-reviewed work from a concurrent role — a
+"smart categorization" feature — which was **excluded** from this release; only
+the reviewed ledger increment ships). Full gate green on the committed trunk:
+
+- `tsc --noEmit` — **clean**
+- `eslint .` — **clean** (0 errors, 0 warnings)
+- `tsx --test` — **49/49 pass**
+- `next build` — **success** (8 static routes prerendered)
+
+All four green → tag cut. A transient build failure observed against the dirty
+working tree (`Cannot find module '@/lib/categorize'`) was traced to the
+concurrent untracked feature, **not** the trunk, and is not part of this release.
+
+## ADR note
+
+Commit `725dcc8` is tagged `[ADR-0006]`, but ADR 0006 is the v0.5.0 home-link
+stabilization guard. The trial-balance decision is distinct and has **no ADR of
+record**; the next free number is `0007`. Backfilling `docs/adr/0007-*` is
+flagged for the engineer — it does not block this release.
+
+## Known issues / carried-over follow-ups
+
+- **`postcss` XSS still open (partial fix)** — GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93 (moderate).
+  Top-level `postcss` is pinned `^8.5.15`, but `next@16.2.6` nests
+  `postcss@8.4.31`, unreachable by the top-level bump. Fix is a one-line
+  `package.json` `overrides` block (`{"postcss": ">=8.5.10"}`) then
+  `npm install` — **not** npm's suggested `next` downgrade. Build-time CSS only;
+  non-blocking for this release. Tracked by the security scan and filed for
+  human decision.
